Package: maxiofs
Version: 0.9.1-beta
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6, adduser
Recommends: nginx, logrotate
Suggests: certbot
Description: High-Performance S3-Compatible Object Storage
 MaxIOFS is a high-performance, S3-compatible object storage system
 built in Go with an embedded React web interface.
 .
 This package includes complete offline documentation in /usr/share/doc/maxiofs/
 including quick start guides, configuration reference, security best practices,
 and complete API documentation.
 .
 Features:
  * Full S3 API compatibility (100% S3 core compatible)
  * Server-Side Encryption (SSE) with AES-256-CTR (v0.4.1+)
  * Comprehensive audit logging system (v0.4.0+)
  * Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) with TOTP
  * Multi-tenancy with resource isolation and quotas
  * Object Lock (WORM) and versioning support
  * Built-in web console for management
  * BadgerDB metadata store for high performance
  * Support for multipart uploads and presigned URLs
  * Lifecycle policies and CORS configuration
  * JWT and S3 signature authentication
  * Prometheus/Grafana monitoring integration
  * Real-time metrics and monitoring
  * Compliance-ready (GDPR, SOC 2, HIPAA, ISO 27001)
  * Single binary deployment
